# recursion-fib

Call overhead, FrameMap construction — naive fib(30).

```scalascript
def fib(n: Int): Int =
  if n <= 1 then n
  else fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2)

def workload(): Int = fib(30)

val WARMUP = 3
val REPS   = 10
var _w = 0
while _w < WARMUP do
  workload()
  _w += 1

val _t0 = System.currentTimeMillis()
var _r = 0
while _r < REPS do
  workload()
  _r += 1
val _ms = System.currentTimeMillis() - _t0
println(s"BENCH_MS: ${_ms.toDouble / REPS}")
```
